rules: Rule1: Provided that the project is government-supported, it follows that either the project has a research permit or, if the project does not have full funding or has partial funding, then the project is approved for expansion.
Rule2: The project is government-supported or the project is privately funded.

Rule3: Whenever the project is privately funded, then either the project has a research permit or, under the condition that the project does not have full funding or has partial funding, the project is approved for expansion.
Rule4: If the sanctuary is established in the region, then the species is not threatened in the area.

Rule17: Either the permit is renewed annually or, if it is not the case that the project has a research permit or that, under the condition that the project does not have full funding or has partial funding, the project is approved for expansion, then the project operations are not cancelled.

Rule24: Under the condition that the project objectives are met, funding continuation is approved.

Rule26: If the study findings are replicated, then the study hypothesis is confirmed.

Rule27: Under the condition that the research methodology is defended, then, if it is not the case that, provided the study hypothesis is confirmed, the research results are validated, then the study conclusions are disputed.

Rule29: Provided that sufficient data is collected, then, under the condition that the project does not have partial funding, the species' population is studied.
Rule30: If the data is analyzed statistically, then, if sufficient data is not collected, the data quality is not reliable.

Rule36: Under the condition that the ranger is available on weekdays, the ranger is assigned to monitoring.
Rule37: Provided that the ranger is available on weekends, the ranger is assigned to patrol.
Rule38: If the ranger is certified in tracking, then the ranger is available on weekdays.
Rule39: The ranger is certified in tracking or the ranger is certified in rescue.

Rule44: Under the condition that it is not the case that the species is protected in the area or not endangered in the area, then the species is threatened in the area.

Rule48: Under the condition that it is not the case that, if the study hypothesis is confirmed, the research results are validated, then the study conclusions are not disputed.
